00074   void I_DFT_NoBarrierSmoother::optimize_vertex_positions(PatchData &pd, 
00075                                                           MsqError &err)
00076   {
00077     MSQ_FUNCTION_TIMER( "I_DFT_NoBarrierSmoother::optimize_vertex_positions" );
00078     
00079       // does the I_DFT_NoBarrier smoothing
00080     MsqFreeVertexIndexIterator free_iter(pd, err);  MSQ_ERRRTN(err);
00081     free_iter.reset();
00082     free_iter.next();
00083       //m is the free vertex.
00084     size_t m=free_iter.value();
00085       //move vertex m
00086     i_dft_no_barrier_smooth_mesh(pd, m, err); MSQ_ERRRTN(err);
00087       //snap vertex m to domain
00088     pd.snap_vertex_to_domain(m,err);
00089   
00090   }

00103   bool I_DFT_NoBarrierSmoother::i_dft_no_barrier_smooth_mesh(
00104     PatchData &pd, size_t free_index, MsqError &err)
00105   {
00106       //get vertex and element arrays
00107     MsqVertex* verts=pd.get_vertex_array(err); MSQ_ERRFALSE(err);
00108     MsqMeshEntity* elems=pd.get_element_array(err);MSQ_ERRFALSE(err);
00109     size_t num_elements = pd.num_elements();
00110       //matrix to store a map for the given corner
00111       // (element/vertex combination) that maps the
00112       //vertex to 0 and the other vertices to 1,2,3
00113     int local_matrix_map[MSQ_MAX_NUM_VERT_PER_ENT];
00114     size_t local_matrix_map_length=MSQ_MAX_NUM_VERT_PER_ENT;
00115     size_t local_matrix_map_used=0;
00116     Vector3D new_position;
00117       //will be used as the denominator
00118     double scale_value = 0.0;
00119     size_t i, j, k;
00120       //Z and Z^(t)
00121     Matrix3D z_mat_transpose;
00122     Matrix3D z_mat[4];
00123       //array of Y's... one for each vertex in this corner.
00124     Matrix3D y_mat[4];
00125       //c_(j,k) for the vertices
00126     double c_scalars[4];
00127       //zeta for this corner
00128     Vector3D zeta_vector;
00129     vector<size_t> elems_verts;
00130       //loop over the two or three dimensions
00131     for(i=0;i<num_elements;++i) {
00132         //actually get the map for this corner...
00133       local_matrix_map_used = elems[i].get_local_matrix_map_about_vertex(
00134         pd, &verts[free_index],local_matrix_map_length, local_matrix_map,err);
00135       MSQ_ERRFALSE(err);
00136       
00137         //get a vector of the vertex indices for this element
00138       elems[i].get_vertex_indices(elems_verts);
00139         //get the W array for this elements
00140       int elem_idx = pd.get_element_index(&elems[i]);
00141       const TargetMatrix* W = pd.targetMatrices.get_element_corner_tags(
00142         &pd, elem_idx, err );      MSQ_ERRFALSE(err);
00143 
00144         //initial c_scalars and zeta_vector to 0.0 and calculate Y for
00145         //each vertex in the this corner.
00146       zeta_vector.set( 0.0, 0.0, 0.0);
00147       for(j=0;j<local_matrix_map_used;++j){
00148         c_scalars[j]=0.0;
00149         if(local_matrix_map[j] < 0){
00150           MSQ_SETERR(err)("Invalid index returned from MsqMeshEntity.\n",
00151                           MsqError::INVALID_STATE);
00152           return false;
00153         }
00154         inv(z_mat[j],W[local_matrix_map[j]]);
00155           //inv(z_mat[j], I);
00156         z_mat_transpose=transpose(z_mat[j]);
00157         matmult( y_mat[j], z_mat[j], z_mat_transpose);
00158           //std::cout<<"\n j "<<j<<"\n";
00159           //std::cout<<"\n"<<y_mat[j]<<"\n";
00160       }
00161         //0 case (c_scalars[0])
00162       for(j=0;j<3;++j){
00163         for(k=0;k<3;++k){
00164           c_scalars[0] += ((y_mat[0])[j][k]);
00165         }
00166         c_scalars[0] += ((y_mat[j+1])[j][j]);
00167       }
00168         //1, 2, and if need 3
00169       for(j=0;j<3;++j){
00170         for(k=0;k<3;++k){
00171           c_scalars[j+1] -= (((y_mat[0])[j][k]) + ((y_mat[j+1])[k][j]));
00172         }
00173         c_scalars[j+1] += ((y_mat[((j+2)%3)+1])[((j+1)%3)][((j+2)%3)]);
00174         c_scalars[j+1] += ((y_mat[((j+1)%3)+1])[((j+2)%3)][((j+1)%3)]);
00175       }
00176         //now do zeta_vector
00177       for(j=0;j<3;++j){
00178         for(k=0;k<3;++k){
00179           zeta_vector[j] += ((z_mat[0])[k][j] - (z_mat[k+1])[k][j]);
00180         }
00181       }
00182     
00183         // accumulate this corner's contribution to the numerator
00184         // and the denominator...
00185       for(j=1;j<local_matrix_map_used;++j){
00186           //std::cout<<"c_k ("<<j<<") ="<<c_scalars[j]<<"\n";
00187           //std::cout<<"x_k ("<<j<<") ="<<verts[elems_verts[ (size_t) local_matrix_map[j]]]<<"\n";
00188         new_position+=verts[elems_verts[ (size_t) local_matrix_map[j]]]
00189           *c_scalars[j];
00190       }
00191       new_position+=zeta_vector;
00192     
00193         //std::cout<<"c_k (0) ="<<c_scalars[0]<<"\n";
00194         //std::cout<<"zeta ="<<zeta_vector<<"\n";
00195       scale_value+=c_scalars[0];
00196     
00197     }
00198     if(scale_value==0.0){
00199       MSQ_SETERR(err)("Invalid accummulation.\n",
00200                       MsqError::INVALID_STATE);
00201       return false;
00202     }
00203       //divide the new position by the denominator and get the
00204       // negative sign into the equation.
00205     new_position/=(-1.0*scale_value);
00206       //debug
00207       //MSQ_DBGOUT(1) << "Original position "<<verts[free_index]<<"\n";
00208       //MSQ_DBGOUT(1) << "New position "<<new_position<<"\n";
00209       //actually set the new position
00210     verts[free_index].set(new_position);
00211   
00212     return true;
00213   }
